        <safety>
          <warning>
            Do not remove actuator without securing nose gear with mechanical downlock pin. Retraction can occur under spring tension or gravity.
          </warning>
          <caution>
            Avoid scratching actuator rod or contaminating ports during handling. Internal seal damage may occur.
          </caution>
          <note>
            This task requires rigging verification and operational gear retraction test after installation (Ref: AMM 32-00-00-710-801).
          </note>
        </safety>
      </preliminaryRqmts>

      <mainProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Open nose gear bay access panels 615NF and 615NL (Ref: AMM 06-00-00 ZONE 210).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Insert nose gear downlock pin (PN: TOOL-NLGLOCK-777) through actuator clevis and side brace attach lug.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Disconnect hydraulic lines from actuator using approved caps/plugs (MS21921-6).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Support actuator with sling. Remove actuator attachment bolts and discard.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Remove actuator from nose gear bay. Clean mating flanges with lint-free cloth and approved solvent (CPC#443).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Install replacement actuator (PN: ACT-NLG-RET-777). Use new bolts and torque to 180 in-lb (Ref: AMM 20-50-00).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Reconnect hydraulic lines using new O-rings (MS28775-222). Confirm seating before torquing fittings to spec.</para>
        </step>
      </mainProcedure>

      <closeProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Remove downlock pin. Reconnect hydraulic power and perform nose gear functional retraction/extension test (Ref: AMM 32-00-00-710-801).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Inspect actuator and lines for leakage under full system pressure.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Record actuator serial number, removal cause, torque values, and test results in aircraft landing gear maintenance log.</para>
        </step>
      </closeProcedure>

