        <safety>
          <warning>
            Actuator may move unexpectedly if hydraulic residual pressure remains. Always depressurize system and cycle controls to vent trapped energy.
          </warning>
          <caution>
            Use care not to damage actuator rod during removal. Scoring or impact will compromise sealing and stroke accuracy.
          </caution>
          <note>
            Actuator replacement requires gear door rigging check upon installation and post-op full gear swing test (Ref: AMM 32-00-00-710-801).
          </note>
        </safety>
      </preliminaryRqmts>

      <mainProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Support gear door with rigging fixture PN: DOORHOLD-777 or equivalent to relieve actuator load.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Tag and disconnect hydraulic lines from actuator body. Cap/plug all fittings (MS21921).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Remove actuator pin retaining clips and remove upper and lower mounting bolts. Retain hardware for reuse if within IPC limits.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Withdraw actuator and place in protective cradle.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Inspect mounting lugs, brackets, and door hinges for signs of wear, elongation, or corrosion (Ref: AMM 32-12-00-220-801).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Install replacement actuator (PN: ACT-MGDR-777). Use retained or new bolts (NAS6204) torqued to 110 in-lb. Apply torque seal.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Reconnect hydraulic lines using new O-rings (MS28775-222). Torque per AMM 20-50-00.</para>
        </step>
      </mainProcedure>

      <closeProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Remove rigging fixture. Re-pressurize hydraulic system and cycle gear doors via GCU input (Ref: AMM 32-61-00-860-801).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Verify full extension/retraction and door seal alignment. Perform door actuator leak check under pressure.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
