        <safety>
          <warning>
            Ensure hydraulic isolation is complete before entering gear bays. Actuators may move if energized.
          </warning>
          <caution>
            Do not rotate or misalign proximity sensors beyond ±0.5 mm from manufacturer-specified gap. Incorrect positioning leads to false gear indications.
          </caution>
          <note>
            All adjustments must be verified using CMS diagnostic menu or direct pin-to-pin measurement (Ref: AMM 92-32-00-720-801).
