          <para>Open gear bay access panel 651AB. Locate uplock and downlock proximity sensors (Ref: IPC 32-61-00, Fig. 4).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Check gap between sensor tip and target surface using feeler gauge set. Standard: 0.030 to 0.060 in. Max limit: 0.080 in.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>If gap exceeds limit, loosen sensor mounting screws and adjust bracket. Re-measure gap and retorque to 35 in-lb (Ref: AMM 20-50-00).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Connect multimeter at electrical rack connector P92–A12 (Ref: WDM 92–32–00). Apply gear override input and observe signal state transitions (HIGH/LOW).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Repeat procedure for NLG and opposite MLG proximity sensors.</para>
